# 2. やりたいこと

Kanade: ...
Kanade: (My future...)
Kanade's Grandmother: <But I believe it's about time for you to start thinking more seriously about your own future.>
Kanade: My future...?
Kanade's Grandmother: <Yes. For starters, what are you going to do after you graduate? You need to begin planning for that.>
Kanade's Grandmother: <That's why I'd like to hear what you think, Kanade. What would you like to do...?>
Kanade: (I've never given it much thought before.)
Kanade: (I've been investing all of my time into composing songs that could save people...)
Kanade: (I don't really know what I want to do...)
Kanade: (I have to keep composing... Anything other than that seems...)
Kanade: Oh...
Mafuyu: I think the bath's ready...
Kanade: Oh, right...
Kanade: You have school tomorrow, don't you, Mafuyu? It's getting late, so why don't you go first?
Mafuyu: Okay.
Mafuyu: <I'm stepping away for a bit.>
Mizuki: <Okie dokie. Enjoy your bath.>
Ena: <Oh, K. About what your envisioning for this song...>
Kanade: <...>
Ena: <K?>
Kanade: <Oh, sorry... Yes?>
Ena: <About this song... Actually, is everything okay? It seems like you've been having trouble concentrating today.>
Mizuki: <Did something happen?>
Kanade: <Oh, um... It's nothing serious...>
Kanade: <My grandma called me today. She told me that I should probably start thinking about what I want to do after I graduate...>
Mizuki: <After you graduate...?>
Kanade: <Yes. I'm not sure what I'm going to do since I've been spending all my time composing music...>
Ena: <I see...>
Ena: <I mean, who actually knows what they want to do in the future?>
Ena: <I haven't even had time to give my own future any serious thought...>
Kanade: <Wait, Enanan, you too?>
Ena: <Yeah. I want to keep drawing, but I don't know what to do about art school and stuff...>
Mizuki: <Oh, right. Art schools are super competitive, right?>
Ena: <Yeah, they are...>
Mizuki: <But it'd be great if you got into a school where you can further pursue art since you're so passionate about it.>
Mizuki: <While we're on the subject, K, is there anything you want to do after you graduate?>
Kanade: <After I graduate...>
Kanade: <Honestly, I kind of want to just keep composing like I've always been...>
Mizuki: <No, that's not what I'm talking about. I'm trying to ask you if...>
Kanade: <...?>
Ena: <Oh, are you asking what she “wants” to do instead of what she feels that she “has” to do...?>
Mizuki: <Yeah! Just like how Enanan wants to keep drawing. Isn't there something like that that really drives you?>
Kanade: <What I want to do...?>
Kanade: (I don't know...)
Kanade: (I have to keep composing. Nothing else really drives me the same way...)
Ena: <K...?>
Kanade: <Oh, sorry... I still can't think of anything else...>
Mizuki: <Okay...>
Mizuki: <To be fair, this is your life we're talking about. You don't want to make any hasty decisions.>
Ena: <I still don't even know what I'm gonna do yet, so I think you should take your time...>
Kanade: <Thank you, I'll do that...>
Ena: <Not gonna lie, I'm a little relieved...>
Kanade: <Huh?>
Ena: <I mean, K, you're always working really hard for the sake of others...>
Ena: <You compose songs in the hopes that you'll save someone. Yuki, for example... You've even done a lot for us.>
Ena: <Which is why I'm glad that you're getting a chance to think about yourself for a change...>
Kanade: <Oh...>
Mizuki: <Yeah, I see what you mean. K does usually put others before herself.>
Ena: <Exactly. I really admire that. I have a huge amount of respect for you...>
Ena: <But I also think you should take more time to do the things that you want, K. The things you think are fun.>
Kanade: <The things I want to do...?>
Kanade: <Okay... Thank you both.>
